% Kirkman's 15 schoolgirls, framed as a Social Golfer instance: 5 groups of 3
% golfers, scheduled for 7 weeks. 15 is not divisible by 4, so this small case
% uses groups of 3 rather than the original problem's groups of 4. At 7 weeks
% every one of the 105 golfer pairs shares a group exactly once (full
% socialisation); 8 weeks is infeasible, so 7 is the maximum.

n_groups   = 5;
group_size = 3;
n_weeks    = 7;
